# SOURCE_PAIRS_ON_SLIT -*-perl-*-

=head1 NAME

SOURCE_PAIRS_ON_SLIT 

=head1 AUTHORS

Frossie Economou <frossie@jach.hawaii.edu>
Paul Hirst <p.hirst@jach.hawaii.edu>

=head1 DESCIPTION

The default 'nod along slit' recipe. Use for point or minimally
extended sources.  Requires you to have allready taken a flat field
and a standard star.

Reduceds the data, estimating the wavelength calibration, optimally
extracts the spectrum from both the main and offset beams, uses the
previously observed standard star for flux calibration.

=cut

# a recipe to reduce observations taken in object-sky pairs

_CGS4_HELLO_
_PAIR_REDUCTION_STEER_
_MASK_BAD_PIXELS_
_SUBTRACT_BIAS_
_FLATFIELD_COADD_INTERLEAVE_
_WAVELENGTH_CALIBRATE_BY_ESTIMATION_
_COADD_PAIRS_AND_GROUP_
_OPTIMALLY_EXTRACT_SPECTRUM_
_DIVIDE_BY_STANDARD_
_FLUX_CALIBRATE_SPECTRUM_
